# Smart Agriculture Docker Deploy Workflow

Follow this rule when the task involves forcing Docker mode, switching from process mode to Docker, or deploying with `docker compose`.

## Current Topology (Docker Mode)

- Domain: `ai.luyaxiang.com`
- Frontdoor: `cloudflared -> nginx 127.0.0.1:5173 -> Docker web 127.0.0.1:3000 -> Docker agent 127.0.0.1:8000`
- Agent port in Docker mode is **8000**, not 18010.
- Repo root: `/Users/mac/Desktop/gago-cloud/code/smart-agriculture`

## Required Workflow

1. Inspect the current state.
   - `git status`
   - Check ports `3000`, `5173`, `18010` with `lsof`
   - `docker ps`

2. Stop process-mode services owned by this repo.
   - Kill `next-server` / `.next/standalone/server.js` on port `3000`
   - Kill `uvicorn app.main:app` on port `18010`
   - Never kill `cloudflared`, `nginx`, or unrelated processes.

3. Pull latest code.
   - Check for local changes before `git pull`

4. Start Docker stack.
   ```bash
   docker compose --env-file .env -f infra/docker/docker-compose.yml up -d --build agent web
   ```
   - Verify: `docker compose --env-file .env -f infra/docker/docker-compose.yml ps`

5. Verify localhost, then domain.
   - `curl http://localhost:3000/api/health`
   - `curl http://localhost:8000/health`
   - login + `POST /api/agent/chat` smoke
   - `curl https://ai.luyaxiang.com/api/health`
   - login + `POST https://ai.luyaxiang.com/api/agent/chat` smoke

## Never Do These

- Do not use port `18010` for the agent health check in Docker mode — use `8000`.
- Do not restart `nginx` or `cloudflared`.
- Do not stop at `/api/health`; full verification requires login + chat smoke.
- Do not run `npm install` or `pip install` manually — Docker build handles dependencies.
